5 or so years ago. we pulled our car to the side of a canyon street somewhere in the mountains along the Cali coast. nahks had packed us a little overnight basket full of the good things. we hiked through bushes and trees until we found this crevice in the rock. he played guitar, i wrote poems, and we stared at the stars. i think we ended up sleeping back in the car half way through the night because it was so damn cold. but even that was delicious. he sent me this photo the other day. made me nostalgic. don’t forget to get nature into your bones every now and then. to adventure, to spend time in places not marked by any trailhead or road. to pull over, and just start hiking. you never know what magic awaits you. @nahkobear

fucking so proud of this one. mostly because our hearts exploded wider and truer with each improvised word that escaped our lips.  with each silent beat that swallowed our breaths.  we stared.  we questioned.  we laughed.  we wept.  we inhaled, and forgot to exhale. we made out. (a LOT). we LOVED.  deeper and purer than i’ve ever loved on any film set.  welcome to a slightly altered autobiography of our lives.  @drakedoremus, you are the warrior of truth in our easily inebriated culture.  my brother in conquest and soul excavation.  my mirrored searcher. @imsebastianstan, you are more than any sentiment could attempt to define.  defying gravity, you are.  and jamie dornan is not on this social media train, but he is all of these things and more rooted in his giant, beautiful, hilarious, and kind heart.  if you love LOVE, if you feel the FEELS ... this one is for you. ♥️💔♥️.

i’ve learned a lot filming down here in south africa. currently 5% of this country’s oceans are protected in Marine Protected Areas. this year they need another 5% to reach their goal of 10% protection by 2020.  and then we tackle 30% by 2030. 
SHARE your love for South Africa's oceans... #Love10x20 and #Love30x30. 
follow @oceanimpactsa for more.  i was so moved by my experience linking up with them last week and learning about the work they’re doing. #southafrica #oceans #ocean #sa #capetown #love10x20 #love30x30

been filming in south africa all month, and have learned quite a bit about their involvement in ocean conservation.  they are so close to achieving their goal of 10% marine protection by the end of 2020. this weekend, i’ll be working with some organizations to bring even more attn to this cause !this is the year for South Africa to make a real change ! check back on my page and @oceanimpactsa for more!

Today I want you to know about an organization that I support that is addressing the root of many of the social issues in our culture.

Based near Seattle, @journeymen encourages compassionate, inspired and resilient young men through nature-based rites of passage, mentorship and community engagement. 
If we empowered our boys and young men to step out of the man box and connect with their hearts, I believe we would know a more peaceful world. A safer world for girls and women. A world where some of our leaders actually address the climate crisis.

All donations made to Journeymen today will be matched 1-1, please give what you can and let's help make their vision a reality:

Men of Integrity.

Respecting All.

Thriving Together.

What am I grateful for? So much, but for now I'll say the 2.3 million people that have joined the call for a strong United Nations Ocean Treaty. Together we're working to protect 30% of the global oceans! 🙏 🔗http://greenpeace.org/protecttheoceans 🔗https://www.oceanunite.org/takeaction/ 
#love30x30 #protectouroceans #oneoceanoneplanet

there is a growing movement supporting 30x30 – from governments, scientists, NGOs and businesses. 
30x30 is a call to action to safeguard at least 30% of the world’s ocean by 2030 through a network of highly safeguarded Marine Protected Areas (MPAs) where no destructive activities like fishing or mining can take place. 
70% of Earth’s surface is Ocean, yet right now, only 2% is fully protected. governments need to accelerate establishing a network of MPAs covering at least 30% of their waters by 2030. 
please join us and share a photo of yourself holding a 30x30 sign and commit to doing your part when it comes to reducing your single use plastic waste. 
we need the world to embrace @OceanUnite’s #Love30x30 Ocean vision. learn more about it up at the link in my bio.
